<Link id="l00087" /><CodeLine lineNumber="87"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00088" /><CodeLine lineNumber="88"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Issues import IDs.  Each ID uniquely corresponds to a tuple of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00089" /><CodeLine lineNumber="89"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (FromModule, GUID, Definition/Declaration).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00090" /><CodeLine lineNumber="90"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00091" /><CodeLine lineNumber="91"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The import IDs make the import list space efficient by referring to each</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00092" /><CodeLine lineNumber="92"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// import with a 32-bit integer ID while maintaining a central table that maps</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00093" /><CodeLine lineNumber="93"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// those integer IDs to tuples of (FromModule, GUID, Def/Decl).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00094" /><CodeLine lineNumber="94"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00095" /><CodeLine lineNumber="95"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// In one large application, a pair of (FromModule, GUID) is mentioned in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00096" /><CodeLine lineNumber="96"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// import lists more than 50 times on average across all destination modules.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00097" /><CodeLine lineNumber="97"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Mentioning the 32-byte tuple:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00098" /><CodeLine lineNumber="98"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00099" /><CodeLine lineNumber="99"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// std::tuple&lt;StringRef, GlobalValue::GUID, GlobalValueSummary::ImportKind&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00100" /><CodeLine lineNumber="100"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00101" /><CodeLine lineNumber="101"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 50 times by value in various import lists would be costly.  We can reduce</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00102" /><CodeLine lineNumber="102"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the memory footprint of import lists by placing one copy in a central table</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00103" /><CodeLine lineNumber="103"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// and referring to it with 32-bit integer IDs.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00104" /><CodeLine lineNumber="104"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00105" /><CodeLine lineNumber="105"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// To save space within the central table, we only store pairs of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00106" /><CodeLine lineNumber="106"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (FromModule, GUID) in the central table.  In the actual 32-bit integer ID,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00107" /><CodeLine lineNumber="107"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the top 31 bits index into the central table while the bottom 1 bit</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00108" /><CodeLine lineNumber="108"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// indicates whether an ID is for GlobalValueSummary::Declaration or</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00109" /><CodeLine lineNumber="109"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// GlobalValueSummary::Definition.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00110" /><CodeLine lineNumber="110" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/functionimporter/importidtable"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">class </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/functionimporter/importidtable/#a5ff8b42892f8fbc5160bd41f8c7e0803">ImportIDTable</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="174"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// The map maintains the list of imports.  Conceptually, it is a collection</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="175"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// of tuples of the form:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="176"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00177" /><CodeLine lineNumber="177"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///   (The name of the source module, GUID, Definition/Declaration)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00178" /><CodeLine lineNumber="178"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00179" /><CodeLine lineNumber="179"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// The name of the source module is the module identifier to pass to the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00180" /><CodeLine lineNumber="180"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// ModuleLoader.  The module identifier strings must be owned elsewhere,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00181" /><CodeLine lineNumber="181"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// typically by the in-memory ModuleSummaryIndex the importing decisions are</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00182" /><CodeLine lineNumber="182"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// made from (the module path for each summary is owned by the index&#39;s module</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00183" /><CodeLine lineNumber="183"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// path string table).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00184" /><CodeLine lineNumber="184" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/functionimporter/importmapty"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">class </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/functionimporter/importmapty/#a224b136d0fb6e75d932859873dccca94">ImportMapTy</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00185" /><CodeLine lineNumber="185"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">public</span><span class="doxyHighlight">:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00186" /><CodeLine lineNumber="186" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/functionimporter/importmapty/#a04d993cd3f6534692c552cfd67fddcdc"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">enum class</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/functionimporter/importmapty/#a04d993cd3f6534692c552cfd67fddcdc">AddDefinitionStatus</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00187" /><CodeLine lineNumber="187"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// No change was made to the list of imports or whether each import should</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00188" /><CodeLine lineNumber="188"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// be imported as a declaration or definition.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00189" /><CodeLine lineNumber="189" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/functionimporter/importmapty/#a04d993cd3f6534692c552cfd67fddcdca4bac8cdf0a968472b519b3b295d0d48b"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/functionimporter/importmapty/#a04d993cd3f6534692c552cfd67fddcdca4bac8cdf0a968472b519b3b295d0d48b">NoChange</a>,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00190" /><CodeLine lineNumber="190"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Successfully added the given GUID to be imported as a definition. There</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00191" /><CodeLine lineNumber="191"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// was no existing entry with the same GUID as a declaration.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00192" /><CodeLine lineNumber="192" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/functionimporter/importmapty/#a04d993cd3f6534692c552cfd67fddcdca157d034f9c98a305eb73776582550027"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/functionimporter/importmapty/#a04d993cd3f6534692c552cfd67fddcdca157d034f9c98a305eb73776582550027">Inserted</a>,</span></CodeLine>
